    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-20T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-20T16:00:00-05:00" n="976"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d976">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1163/1119: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-20T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 20, 1941—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>516. Peiping’s despatch no. 43, June 21, 1941,<note n="60" xml:id="d976fn1">Not
                        printed.</note> reported Japanese trespass on American property at Tsining,
                    Shantung, removal of an American flag therefrom, and the looting thereof.</p>
                <p>The Department suggests that the Embassy place on record with the Foreign Office
                    our view that the Japanese Consul General’s reply of June 12, 1941 to the
                    American Vice Consul at Tsinan<note n="60" xml:id="d976fn2">Not printed.</note>
                    is unsatisfactory and request that the Foreign Office cause a further
                    investigation and report on the incident to be made.</p>
                <p>Sent to Tokyo via Shanghai. Repeated to Chungking and Peiping. Peiping please
                    forward code text to Tsinan by mail.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
